Great recipe....I decided to follow someone's review and sped up the steps. I also chopped the onion, fennel, cut my potatoes into small cubes and my shrimp into thirds. I also pureed the soup after potatoes were done...then again after cooking tomatoes and finally a third time after shrimp was done cooking. I made sure I left about 1/3 of the shrimp in big chunks. I only added about 1/2 cup whipping cream. The soup came out great.My two toddlers actually ate it too! Definitely a soup worth making...a nice one for company too. :)

