Rating: 4
I have made this twice now. First time it took me almost 4 hours, second time, only an hour! Don't do the instructions in order. Do this: peel shrimp and chop tops off fennel. Start the stock with the shells and fennel. At the same time, put on the bacon. The bacon browning and the stock should take about the same amount of time: 20 mins or so. While they are cooking, chop the fennel and onion. After you put that on, clean and slice the shrimp. Then do the potatos. Then when it's time, drain the stock directly into the big pot. Follow the rest of the directions as directed, but this simultaneous-tasking cut my time a ton! and has made this something i can cook anytime now. My last variation i added a pound of bay scallops and didn't add the cream... it turned out delicious too, and lighter! This is going into my rotation of soups...

